MBOMBELA – The long-time leader of Mozambique’s main opposition party, Afonso Dhlakama, has reportedly died in his home country, other media outlets reported on Thursday. The former guerilla leader was 65 years old. Lowvelder has, during recent investigations into the country’s security situation, noted concern among certain government officials over the tense situation between his and the ruling party. READ MORE:  Isis fighters infiltrate neighbouring Mozambique It is understood that Dhlakama was found dead at his home in Gorongosa. *Read Friday’s print edition of Lowvelder for our investigation into the anarchy gripping parts of our neighbouring state. ALSO READ: Mozambique on the brink of civil war yet again